<br>
We'll do this on the 22nd of July, starting at 2 pm Central time. We will begin gathering and staging at 1 pm Central time at the fake wall in the Ice Giant fortress in Everfrost. This means I will start gathering people together into groups at 1, and at 2 pm or very shortly after, we will zone into Permafrost and begin the hunt. Binds should be in Halas, or in Qeynos for the evil classes that might be KOS in the Everfrost area. I'll begin announcing all the mixer hunts in the week before the hunt is to take place. Any Council guild members can participate in this, as well as anyone else who wishes to do so. All loot that is rare will be lottoed by me, and only those who can and will use it (i.e. don't already have something better or a duplicate) will be allowed to lotto for it. Any Council guild leaders who wish to have one of their guild members lead a group, please let me know on this board. Also, if any of the people who will be involved in this raid want to volunteer to do teleports, binds or invis for those who will need it, please post here as well.<br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
The Silver Daggers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvanissa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vanissa</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/9/00 6:56:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theunderworld.net/kson/vanissahead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Permafrost Dungeon Mixer Hunt</span><hr size=1> Some information I put together for the Kindred Souls of Norrath raid on Permafrost we had back in June.  It ended up being a non-event as we only had four attendees and couldn't get very far.<br>
