<br>
Upon entering the dungeon, we are to kill everything in our path up to and including the flag room. Once the flag room is cleared, we clear a few of the spawns between the flag room and the first main room between the flag room and the preacher room. Then we move to the Preacher's room itself. Once there, we will wait out a few spawns to attempt to kill the Goblin Preacher. His common drop is the Cold Iron Morning Star, and the rare is the coveted Runed Circlet. After dispatching him, we go through the dungeon to the Archeologist's room, where we will kill the Goblin Archeologist, who drops the Archeologist's Pack or the Dented Brass Mask. From there we proceed past the main gate to the Alchemist's room, where we will take out the Goblin Alchemist. He drops the mammoth cloak or the mammoth leggings. <br>
<br>
After the alchemist, it's a fight through to the Jail, where we will kill the Jail Master. He has the wooly silk net, and for his rare, the Etched Ivory charm. From there we will move back through the jail to the Frozen King's/scryer room, and kill the Goblin Scryer, who drops the Ice Crystal staff or the wolf fur slippers. <br>
<br>
From the scryer's room, we go back to the main gate, and into the tough part of the dungeon. We have to be really careful here, as the Ice Giants are close to this area. We must keep our groups together here or risk serious trains of mobs that will kill us all. The King's room has a number of spawns, including the Elite Honor Guards and/or the Elite Goblin Guards. The elite goblin guards occasionally drop the icy greaves. The Honor guards drop the silver axes (1h or 2h). The King will drop either the symbol of loyalty to Vox, or the White Wolf Hide cloak. Once the goblin king is dead, the raid will be over, and hopefully will be called a success. <br>
<br>
Any players are welcome to come, whether Council of Guilds members, non-Council members, or independent players. Anyone from level 26-35 are welcome to come. Any CoG guild members that you can recommend in this level range to be group leaders? <br>
